# Styling & Color System Guidelines

To ensure robust theme support (light and dark modes) and maintain consistent UI styling across components, follow these guidelines for colors:

## 1. Prefer Shadcn Color Variables

Always use the standard Shadcn Tailwind utility mappings. Avoid hardcoding custom hex values or project-specific colors unless there is a mandatory branding requirement.

| Tailwind Class | Mapped CSS Variable | Usage |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `bg-background` / `text-foreground` | `--background` / `--foreground` | Main page body, cards, and text |
| `bg-card` / `text-card-foreground` | `--card` / `--card-foreground` | Container cards and boxes |
| `bg-primary` / `text-primary-foreground` | `--primary` / `--primary-foreground` | Call-to-actions, highlighted active states |
| `bg-secondary` / `text-secondary-foreground` | `--secondary` / `--secondary-foreground` | Subtle secondary actions and buttons |
| `bg-muted` / `text-muted-foreground` | `--muted` / `--muted-foreground` | Disabled, placeholder, or deactivated elements |
| `border-border` | `--border` | Dividers, borders, and lines |
| `bg-input` | `--input` | Input borders and elements |
| `ring-ring` | `--ring` | Active focus rings and states |

## 2. When to Use Custom Brand Colors

- **Rule:** Only use custom brand colors (e.g., `gold`, `gold-bright`, `gold-dim`, `obsidian`, `char`, `ivory`) when implementing specific branded components or layouts that *must* maintain a specific color combination regardless of light/dark themes (e.g., a signature luxury gold border CTA button or fixed dark hero page).
- **Rule:** If custom styling is used, prefer accessing them via Tailwind custom theme variables (e.g., `text-gold`, `bg-obsidian`) rather than raw hex codes like `#08080a`.

## 3. Ensure Light/Dark Theme Adaptability

By using standard Shadcn color variables, components will automatically adapt when switching between light and dark modes. Avoid hardcoding styles that prevent theme switching.
